      summary_zh: "条件扩散模型同时执行去噪、超分辨率、各向异性校正 —— 用单一通用方案取代 Topaz-Denoise、DeepEMhancer、EMReady 的拼凑。",
      problem: `<p>Cryo-EM post-processing is fragmented: <strong>Topaz-Denoise (Bepler, Nat Commun 2020)</strong> for denoising via N2N; <strong>DeepEMhancer (Comm Biol 2021)</strong> for sharpening; <strong>EMReady2 (bioRxiv 2025)</strong> for general improvement; <strong>DiffModeler (2024)</strong> for backbone tracing. None handle full pipeline. Each needs its own checkpoint and may produce inconsistent outputs when chained.</p>`,
      problem_zh: `<p>冷冻电镜后处理分散：<strong>Topaz-Denoise (Bepler, Nat Commun 2020)</strong> N2N 去噪；<strong>DeepEMhancer (Comm Biol 2021)</strong> 锐化；<strong>EMReady2 (bioRxiv 2025)</strong> 通用改善；<strong>DiffModeler (2024)</strong> 骨架追踪。没有方法处理完整流水线。每工具需自己 checkpoint，串联时可能不一致。</p>`,
      unique_advantage: `<strong>Why ONLY Plan A enables this:</strong> Training a multi-task diffusion model requires paired examples for each task. Plan A is the only dataset with (real, simulated) pairs at 11K scale AND Gold/Silver/Bronze tiers for resolution-aware behavior.`,
      unique_advantage_zh: `<strong>为什么只有 Plan A 能支撑：</strong>训练多任务扩散模型需每种任务的配对样本。Plan A 是唯一在 11K 规模提供（真实，模拟）配对 + Gold/Silver/Bronze 分档的数据集。`,
      approach: `<p><strong>Single conditional latent diffusion model:</strong></p><ul><li>3D VAE encoder/decoder for compact latent space</li><li>Diffusion in latent, conditioned on: (a) source map embedding, (b) target resolution, (c) operation token (denoise/sharpen/SR/anisotropy)</li><li>Trained on Plan A's 11K experimental + ChimeraX pairs with multiple task variants per entry (synthetic noise injection, resolution down-sampling, anisotropy simulation)</li></ul><p>Flow Matching variant for fast inference (5-step vs 50-step DDPM).</p>`,
      approach_zh: `<p><strong>单一条件 latent 扩散模型：</strong></p><ul><li>3D VAE encoder/decoder 形成紧凑 latent 空间</li><li>扩散在 latent 空间，条件为：(a) 源图嵌入，(b) 目标分辨率，(c) 操作 token（denoise/sharpen/SR/anisotropy）</li><li>在 Plan A 11K 实验 + ChimeraX 配对上训练，每条目多种任务变体（合成噪声、分辨率降采样、各向异性模拟）</li></ul><p>Flow Matching 变体快速推理（5 步 vs 50 步 DDPM）。</p>`,
      key_challenges: `<p><strong>Challenge 1: ChimeraX simulated maps lack CTF/anisotropy — not a "perfect ground truth". Solution:</strong>Two-stage: Stage 1 uses synthetic data with known CTF deconvolution;Stage 2 real EMDB + ChimeraX targets fine-tune。N2N + supervised mixed loss prevents overfitting.</p><p><strong>Challenge 2: Hallucination risk:</strong>the diffusion model may fabricate details.<strong>Solution:</strong>(a) PHENIX CC validation, not just PSNR；(b) output per-voxel uncertainty map；(c) strictly separate "display" vs "modeling" output modes.</p>`,
      key_challenges_zh: `<p><strong>Challenge 1: ChimeraX 模拟图缺 CTF/各向异性：</strong><strong>Solution:</strong>分两阶段 — Stage 1 合成数据学 CTF 反卷积；Stage 2 真实 EMDB + ChimeraX 目标 fine-tune。N2N + 监督混合 loss。</p><p><strong>Challenge 2: 幻觉风险：</strong><strong>Solution:</strong>(a) PHENIX CC 校验；(b) 输出每体素 uncertainty map；(c) 严格区分"显示用" vs "建模用" mode。</p>`,
      evaluation: `<ul><li>Metrics: FSC improvement, Q-score gain, EMRinger, MapQ, PSNR</li><li>Compare vs: Topaz-Denoise, CryoCARE, DeepEMhancer, EMReady2, CryoTEN, DiffModeler</li><li>Downstream: ModelAngelo accuracy improvement on restored maps</li><li>Hallucination check:sandbox-degraded high-quality map test</li></ul>`,
      evaluation_zh: `<ul><li>Metrics: FSC improvement, Q-score gain, EMRinger, MapQ, PSNR</li><li>Compare vs: Topaz-Denoise, CryoCARE, DeepEMhancer, EMReady2, CryoTEN, DiffModeler</li><li>Downstream: improvement in ModelAngelo accuracy on restored maps</li><li>Hallucination check: hallucination test: verify no new structural features are introduced when applied to sandbox-degraded high-quality maps</li></ul>`,
      publication: `<p>🎯 <strong>Target: Nature Methods</strong>. Replacing 4 common tools with a unified solution fits Nature Methods' preference for disruptive methodology. DiffModeler 2024 in Nat Methods validates diffusion models. <strong>Timeline:</strong> 9-12 months.</p>`,
      publication_zh: `<p>🎯 <strong>目标：Nature Methods</strong>. Replacing 4 common tools with a unified solution fits Nature Methods' preference for disruptive methodology. DiffModeler 2024 validates diffusion models in cryo-EM. <strong>Timeline:</strong> 9-12 months.</p>`,
